# Naming Conventions

## Files

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| React Components | PascalCase | `FeatureCard.tsx`, `FormField.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase + `use` prefix | `useFeature.ts`, `useForm.ts` |
| Stores | camelCase + `use` prefix | `useNotificationStore.ts`, `useCartStore.ts` |
| Services | camelCase | `feature.ts`, `auth.ts` |
| Types | camelCase | `feature.ts`, `api.ts` |
| Utils | camelCase | `formatters.ts`, `cn.ts` |
| Config | camelCase | `api.ts`, `queryKeys.ts` |

## Folders

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Screens (mobile) | PascalCase | `FeatureScreen/`, `AuthForm/` |
| Pages (web, Next.js) | camelCase | `feature/`, `settings/` |
| Shared folders | camelCase | `hooks/`, `services/`, `utils/` |
| Stores | camelCase | `stores/` |
| Config / constants | camelCase | `config/`, `constants/` |

## No Redundant Suffixes

The folder provides context — drop suffixes that repeat it:

✅ `services/feature.ts` — folder says it's a service
❌ `services/featureService.ts` — redundant

✅ `hooks/useForm.ts` — file name says it's a hook
❌ `hooks/useFormHook.ts` — redundant

## Index Files

Always use `index.ts` for directory exports:

```typescript
// components/features/feature/index.ts
export { FeatureCard } from './FeatureCard';
export { FeatureList } from './FeatureList';
export { FeatureForm } from './FeatureForm';
```

## Type Naming

| Kind | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Entity | PascalCase | `Feature`, `User` |
| Props | Component + `Props` | `FeatureCardProps` |
| Form state | Feature + `FormData` | `FeatureFormData` |
| API input | Feature + `Input` | `FeatureInput` |
| API response | `ApiResponse<T>` | `ApiResponse<Feature[]>` |
